PLACE steak in a large heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag; add steak sauce and pepper. Seal bag; chill 30 minutes, turning once. Remove steak from marinade, discarding marinade. MASH avocado in a small bowl. Stir in lemon juice and remaining ingredients; cover and chill. GRILL steaks, covered with grill lid, over medium-high heat (350 to 400 degrees) 7 minutes on each side, or to desired degree of doneness. Serve with guacamole.